						<section class="wrapper style4 container">

<h4>攀</h4>

<h1>夹在石与骨之间
<br>角质层渐失柔软
<br>岩壁上，小心翼翼
<br>偶尔的褶皱托举着
<br>发烫的黑色胶底
<br>指腹的圈圈涟漪
<br>也被扰动</h1>

<h1>系在绳上的
<br>是对自由的最后让步吗
<br>凝滞的介质
<br>在失重的瞬间浸入
<br>速率归零时，出定
<br>坠落前后
<br>进出虚空的准许
<br>也被悄悄系上</h1>

<h1>上山的最快路径
<br>难道是沿这条彩色绳索
<br>水凿扶手的天工
<br>也把碎沙风化
<br>填入轻刻的凹痕
<br>轻轻拂去
<br>就放得下一根指头</h1>

<h1>树冠间跃迁的风险
<br>直立行走的猿猴无需染指
<br>悠久的攀爬之瘾
<br>仍沿着双螺旋阶梯
<br>走到今天的丛林
<br>对景致的垂涎
<br>也许是新的</h1>

<h1>收回的目光也照在
<br>花岗石的纹理
<br>而触顶的渴望
<br>进化论未曾预测
<br>甚者，抵达前的回首
<br>成了更艰难的命题</h1>

<h1>也许只是暂时攀够了
<br>便转身而去
<br>在日落中下降
<br>和着月光睡在岩石上
<br>醒来时山还在那里</h1>

<br>
<br>
<br>
<h4>Climb (translated by ChatGPT)</h4>

<h1>Sandwiched between stone and bone,
<br>The stratum corneum gradually loses its softness.
<br>On the rock face, cautiously,
<br>Occasional folds cradle the hot, black rubber soles.
<br>Circles of ripples on the fingertips too, 
<br>Disturbed.</h1>

<h1>Tied to the rope,
<br>Is it the final concession to freedom?
<br>Stagnant medium, immersed in the moment of weightlessness.
<br>When the speed returns to zero, out of samadhi
<br>Before and after the fall,
<br>The permission to enter and exit the void is also attached.</h1>

<h1>Is the fastest way up the mountain
<br>Surely along this colorful rope?
<br>Nature’s engineering chisels artisanal handrail,
<br>But also weather the broken sand.
<br>Fill the lightly carved hollows,
<br>Gently brushing them away,
<br>A finger can be placed.</h1>

<h1>The risk of leaping among the treetops,
<br>Need not taint the upright-walking apes.
<br>The long-standing addiction to climbing,
<br>Still follows the double-helix staircase,
<br>To today's jungle, though
<br>The craving for the scenery, perhaps is new.</h1>

<h1>The withdrawn gaze also falls on
<br>Texture of the granite,
<br>And the desire to touch the summit,
<br>Unpredicted by evolution.
<br>Indeed, looking back before reaching the destination,
<br>Has become a more difficult proposition.</h1>

<h1>Perhaps it's just a temporary climb,
<br>Then turn and leave.
<br>Descending in the sunset,
<br>Sleeping on the rocks quilted by the moonlight.
<br>When you wake up, the mountain is still there.</h1>

